reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Saved a lot of money
reviews.reviewText: I saved close to $100 vs other batteries. It fit my Harley Davidson Dyna Super Glide. Once I charged it, it has worked wonderfully.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They Started the Harley's
reviews.reviewText: Battery cost was 65% less than dealer or local retailer. No Issues, EZ to install the battery in motorcycle, confirmed power, fired up the bike and went for a ride. Still holding a charge. Warranty as good as the dealership and left $$$ in my pocket for several tank fill ups of Premium Fuel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fits but not all parts come with battery
reviews.reviewText: The battery turned over my '13 Fatboy Lo, but not until after I adjusted the terminals to get the nuts in place. The battery didn't come with new bolts and nuts, so had to use the hardware off the stock setup. Again, it started up fine, but not until after some careful adjusting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: "Amazon confirmed Fit" stated it would not fit my 2012 FLD Switchback, but I checked the case size prior to ordering and the fit was perfect. Out of the box, it started the bike in 40 F temperature easily. It came with nuts and bolts and was an easy install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars piece of junk out the box
reviews.reviewText: dont buy this piece of junk installed in my harley ,dead on arrival , charged wud not hold charge , thought sumthing else was wrong took my bike to the harley shop , said battery was trash even brand new , cudnt even be charged , these people know they selling junk , buy american people , might cost a little more , but much better product

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fitment, started my bike right up!
reviews.reviewText: This fit perfectly on my 2001 Harley Wide glide. Im unsure of the other reviews with fitment issues but this was the exact same size as my “premium brand” 20HL group sized battery. Packaging was good. Came with all new needed hardware and spacers. Did not test cold cranking amps as other users have, but it started my bike out of the box in no time as any new battery should. Terminals are kinda flimsy, as obviously posted in the ad photos, but that doesn't effect functionality, just don’t crazily over tighten them, and you shouldn’t have issues. What do you expect for the price.Have rode a few miles on this so far with no issues.Longevity and internal durability is the only undetermined point of this battery. Im hoping to get a few seasons out of it. I have bought value batteries in the past that have lasted just as long as the “premium” ones. Will update review if failed prematurely.
